This configuration file splits the aries links metrics in gpcdr into separate files.
You will need this prior to CLE 5.2 UP05 (See the cray_system_sampler man page).

# As root:
#Set environment variable GPCDRINIT_CONF to point to desired gpcdr config file

Example:
export GPCDRINIT_CONF=/XXX/util/gemini/gpcdr/gpcdr-init_split.conf

# Remove nic and link metrics
Example:
/opt/cray/gni-gpcdr-utils/default/sbin/gpcdr-ctl -M nic -D
/opt/cray/gni-gpcdr-utils/default/sbin/gpcdr-ctl -M links -D

NOTE after you have installed this version, you will instead have to do:

/opt/cray/gni-gpcdr-utils/default/sbin/gpcdr-ctl -M nic -D
/opt/cray/gni-gpcdr-utils/default/sbin/gpcdr-ctl -M linktraffic -D
/opt/cray/gni-gpcdr-utils/default/sbin/gpcdr-ctl -M linstalled -D
/opt/cray/gni-gpcdr-utils/default/sbin/gpcdr-ctl -M linksendstatus -D
/opt/cray/gni-gpcdr-utils/default/sbin/gpcdr-ctl -M linkrecvstatus -D


